
	SemEval-2007 Task 10: English Lexical Substitution Task
		In this paper we describe the English Lexical Substitution task for SemEval.
		In the task, annotators and systems find an alternative substitute word or phrase for a target word in context.
		The task involves both finding the synonyms and disambiguating the context.Participating systems are free to use any lexical resource.
		There is a subtask which re quires identifying cases where the word isfunctioning as part of a multiword in the sen tence and detecting what that multiword is.
	
	
			Word sense disambiguation (WSD) has been de scribed as a task in need of an application.
			Whilstresearchers believe that it will ultimately prove useful for applications which need some degree of se mantic interpretation, the jury is still out on this point.
			One problem is that WSD systems have been tested on fine-grained inventories, rendering the task harder than it need be for many applications (Ide and Wilks, 2006).
